		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Balto.</placeName> <date>Nov. 12&#47;62</date></p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I intended long ago to an<lb/>swer your letter &#38; to transmit to you<lb/> the small amount which I owe you&#44;<lb/> but sickness &#38; all kind of unprovided<lb/> disturbances&#44; made me delay it till<lb/> to day.  I hope therefore you will<lb/> excuse me.</p>
				<p>With regret I have seen by your<lb/> letter that you have also been sick&#44;<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> so is it with us...<add>Hebrew</add><lb/> Thank to God&#44; that you &#38; I&#44; have<lb/> been restored to health &#38; spared per&#45;<lb/>haps for a few years longer.</p>
				<p>In regard to your remark&#44; that the<lb/> Occident for me was sent back to you</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>I can only assure you <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> for it would have been not only<lb/> against all courtesy&#44; but even un&#45;<lb/>grateful&#44; for you have never charged<lb/> me anything for it&#44; &#38; why should I<lb/> offend you &#38; be &#160;&#160;&#63; <add>Hebrew</add><lb/> I thought&#44; that at this hard times<lb/> you don&#39;t send any more gratis<lb/> exemplars&#44; &#38; I excused you perfectly&#44;<lb/> but I have never sent any of your<lb/> copies back.</p>
				<p><sic>Inclosed</sic> please to <del>accept</del> receive<lb/> &#36;6.15&#47;100 as the pay for the books &#38; please<lb/> to send me again in <sic>Comission</sic></p>
				<p>4 Doz. first Catechism or Bible History</p>
				<p>4 &#8220; Road to faith&#44; by <persName>Nathan</persName></p>
				<p>4 &#8220; Scriptures by <persName>Peixotto</persName></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>Please send them soon&#44; &#38; without<lb/> expenses&#44; &#38; as soon&#44; as they shall be<lb/> sold&#44; I will send you again the<lb/> amount.</p>
				<p>Wishing you perfect health &#38;<lb/> <add>Hebrew</add> I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Your faithful</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">A. Guinzburg</persName></p>
		</body>
